</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/18/03 4:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Policing me?</span><hr size=1> Except this isn't a governement.<br>
<br>
A rotation is an agreement between the parties that can kill a mobile in Everquest. It regulates the ethics and morals that the involved parties stick to when dealing with each other over the spawn in question. It is not a law, it's not an absolute. Note that I use the words 'the involved parties' here. I do this because until you are killing said mobile the rotation agreement doesn't concern you and doesn't effect you or your gameplay one jot.<br>
<br>
The key to two parties making an agreement is that they adress each other when doing so, not some third party. If I want to buy my friends cd player but do not have as much cash as he wants for it at the time and we agree that I'll pay him twenty dollars a month for it until he has all of the asking price then I don't send an email to Nyko Makasumi in South Korea asking if I can do this. It doesn't concern her. She may through some unlikely chain of incredible events end up buying it from me when I in turn want to sell it and I may offer her the same deal. Then again, she could say that she doesn't have even twenty dollars a month but that she can swing fifteen a month instead.<br>
<br>
I could go on and on turning rotational agreements into easily understood allegories but others have done so, I've done it once already and it still wont help will it?<br>
<br>
You want to argue from the standpoint that there is a governing body that stipulates rules in the interest of every individual on the server. That way lies fertile ground for the whole downtrodden masses with their just and moral outcry against the supressing elitists deal. I don't blame you really, it's a good and easy launch for a debate, it's just that it is inaccurate.<br>
<br>
What exists is an agreement between the guilds able to kill a mobile in Everquest. Furthermore, this is a board that publicizes said agreement so that others that are interested in joining the agreement in harmony with it's ethics may see what is required of them. They are free not to do so by relating to the mobile in question in any way the want. There is no law or rule that a kill has to go according to the rotational agreement if you are not part of the guilds that have entered into the agreement and therefore it's a silly notion to have a law that requires them to let anyone else see their discussion of the same agreement. If you really want to argue from your current platform then what we are now dealing with is attempted invasion of privacy.<br>
<br>
What is the RTA? It's a collection of agreements. NB, FK, TL and BotS agree to share mobile A in a manner that satisfies them all, or at least doesn't unfairly benefit one over the others <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Far Seekers, Muse and Merriment, Ring of Dragons and Raging Fury decides to share mobile B in a different way.<br>
<br>
What, Norrath Travel Bureau wants to kill mobile B also? Here you go guys, this is how we are doing it, if you do it by our standards we'll extend you the same courtesies as we do each other. Note the 'if', it implies choice. What, Norrath Travel Bureau notifies us that we should change this aspect of our agreement. Oh, do they want to kill mobile B also? No...they can't. I don't understand, why should we change the way we do things then, surely it's our concern and not theirs? Well they said they play on the same server...<br>
<br>
Are the rotational agreements the best way of doing things? Debatable, I'm sure. They do however provide one of the least stressful and confrontational athmospheres among all of the different servers. Good or bad, the agreements reward a cooperational spirit instead of an agressive one. So that is the much vaunted spirit of the Rathe.<br>
<br>
I admired your passion at first and it's not every day you see well written posts on this board but it is starting to get a little predictable and tired. Is it passion or self confirmation at this point? You will read my post and if you decide to adress it you'll keep on doing it from the same platform. I.E. there will be alot more reasoning involving the proper way a ruling body sets up a control system in order to insure impartialness in it's dealings with it's subordinates. In the end, you want a say in something that doesn't concern you, either by yourself or via proxy. You want to police my dealings in an area that has no contact surfaces with you, your game or your actions in it?<br>
<br>
Your guild leader seems fond of the saying 'my right to swing my arm ends where your nose starts'. Right now I am feeling the draft and you are dangerously close to stepping on my individual freedoms here. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ruldarswiftnote>Ruldar Swiftnote</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/18/03 5:23 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Elemental planes forum</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Let someone else have access that doesn't have any concern with those legitimate conversations, but who can act as a overseers for the community.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>While I respect Roggulbuk far more than I ever will any of you, one person is hardly 'fair and impartial' representation ...but nice try.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->And here I would have thought the original request was for one person.  Someone is singular, isn't it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roggulbuk>Roggulbuk</A></