Example:  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm52.showMessage?topicID=15.topic" target="top">Can't team up on flag mobs</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Do I need to go on?  Every 'agreement' you make, and make no mistake about who exactly made these laws, we have to abide by.  So, tell me, how does this not affect my gameplay one jot?  It is hardly as if we are completely free to do as we wish until such time as we can kill such and such mobile in Everquest ...so how can you sit there and say, the rotation agreements don't concern us unless we are on that rotation?  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I could go on and on turning rotational agreements into easily understood allegories but others have done so, I've done it once already and it still wont help will it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->At least not until you come up with a valid analogy that is remotely relevant to the argument at hand.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You want to argue from the standpoint that there is a governing body that stipulates rules in the interest of every individual on the server. That way lies fertile ground for the whole downtrodden masses with their just and moral outcry against the supressing elitists deal. I don't blame you really, it's a good and easy launch for a debate, it's just that it is inaccurate.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I don't argue that standpoint at all.  I argue from the standpoint that there IS a governing body that stipulates rules the community must abide by (whether or not they are in the interest of every individual is highly suspect) behind closed doors, with no accountability whatsoever.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Furthermore, this is a board that publicizes said agreement so that others that are interested in joining the agreement in harmony with it's ethics may see what is required of them. They are free not to do so by relating to the mobile in question in any way the want. There is no law or rule that a kill has to go according to the rotational agreement if you are not part of the guilds that have entered into the agreement and therefore it's a silly notion to have a law that requires them to let anyone else see their discussion of the same agreement.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Are you kidding me?  Have you even LOOKED at the RTA etiquette page recently?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They are free not to do so by relating to the mobile in question in any way the want.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Lets talk about this freedom, this choice, that you speak of.  Lets see ...I'm the guild leader of a guild ...I can either 'choose' to be a member of the RTA (and therefore be dictated to by it's laws\etiquette that are created by a minority group consisting of the top 4 guilds) ...or I can, what?  What exactly is my choice here?  Not join the RTA and not abide by their rules? Move their entire guild to another server?  This idea is so far-fetched, it is laughable.  Cmon, people, all together now, what would happen if a guild 'chose' that it didn't want to abide by the rules of the RTA?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you really want to argue from your current platform then what we are now dealing with is attempted invasion of privacy.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Dear God, someone shoot me, please.  The RTA doesn't recognize a constitution, a bill of rights, or anything remotely resembling a freedom of information act ...but it has no problem invoking a law of privacy?  Seriously, omg, I'm in tears, but I can't tell if they because I'm laughing or crying.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Are the rotational agreements the best way of doing things? Debatable, I'm sure. They do however provide one of the least stressful and confrontational athmospheres among all of the different servers. Good or bad, the agreements reward a cooperational spirit instead of an agressive one. So that is the much vaunted spirit of the Rathe.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I 100% agree with you on this point, as it pertains to the calendaring and technical scheduling system of the RTA.  If it was truly all about the fact that everyone has to stand in line for their fair and equal turn at content, we would not be having this conversation ...but it isn't, is it?  You don't simply put A_Firebeetle_01 on rotation and say, &quot;here, share&quot; ...You say, &quot;here, share, and oh btw ....&quot;.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I admired your passion at first and it's not every day you see well written posts on this board but it is starting to get a little predictable and tired. Is it passion or self confirmation at this point? You will read my post and if you decide to adress it you'll keep on doing it from the same platform. I.E. there will be alot more reasoning involving the proper way a ruling body sets up a control system in order to insure impartialness in it's dealings with it's subordinates. In the end, you want a say in something that doesn't concern you, either by yourself or via proxy. You want to police my dealings in an area that has no contact surfaces with you, your game or your actions in it?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->...and, once again, read anything on the so called 'etiquette' page and keep telling me how any of this 'has no contact surfaces with you, your game or your actions in it&quot;.<br>
<br>
The difference between you and me is that I gain absolutely nothing personally from this exchange, other than the knowledge that I am attempting to create a fair and impartial policy making system with the best interests of the community as a whole.  You are protecting what's yours ...I understand that ...but I believe with my very soul that it is wrong for a minority group of people to make policy that DOES AFFECT EVERYONE behind closed doors with no accountability to anyone other than themselves.<br>
<br>
The only argument you can claim is that it doesn't affect me.  I believe I have counter-pointed by example of the etiquette page that those 'policies' do affect me without my ever being on any rotation; therefore, we do deserve that those discussions take place with appropriate non-rotation representation.  Am I asking that *I* get access to that forum?  No.  Am I asking to *handpick* the people who would have access?  No.  The RTA Representatives are chosen by their respective guilds ...in affect, the community, and that is fine with me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you dont trust Rogg as a smaller guild Rep who is an admin then I really dont know who you can trust. Rogg is one of the most trustworthy people i know in this game and has always been straightforward with everyone.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Unlike you, I would never dream of placing Roggulbuk in the position that you are all so happy to put him in.  He has friends and loyalties on both sides of this fence and placing him in the middle is incredibly unfair to him, no matter what hat he is wearing.  The very second a discrepency comes up, you are going to have people from all sides attacking him as being partial to the other side ...something that, I might add, has already occured with the forum, and you would have to be a serious ass to wish that kind of crap on anyone.  I am not doubting this trustworthiness and integrity ...I simply wish to spare him the aggravation and frustration later of having to deal with that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>By doubting his trust you show me that you in fact dont deserve either my trust or my respect, which i doubt you care about, and as i said before we arent going to change your mind and you arent going to change ours.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->On this, we can be in 100% agreement ...I don't care what you think of me personally, just as I would not expect you to care what I may think of you personally.  I am merely trying to debate an issue on which you and I are on two different sides.  You are wrong in the assumption that I would not change my mind if given enough acceptable reasons to do so ...unfortunately, &quot;because we said so!&quot; doesn't cut it ...&quot;because we are more entitled to do so!&quot; doesn't cut it ...and &quot;because this is the way it has always been!&quot; certainly won't do it.  <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->These are stupid ideas and these people should be given a damn good thrashing with a clue stick.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.clanbashemded.org" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.clanbashemded.org/images/rigsig.gif" style="border:0;height:150;width:300;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=438887" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:white;font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;">Magelo Profile</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vilgan>Vilgan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/19/03 11:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Elemental planes forum</span><hr size=1> This thread should be renamed &quot;conspiracy theorists of the world unite&quot; and be moved to the flame board already. points been made, I think its pretty obvious minds aren't going to get changed, and most of the posts have been personal attacks for the last 10 pages. I wish I had a picture of a rotten and decaying horse getting beaten by Rigorre and company so we could remove the need for further conspiracy theories.<br>
